description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/oscore.c
Lines: 1546-1599

The find_coap_payload_marker function returns int but the position is computed from size_t:

```c
static int find_coap_payload_marker(const uint8_t *data, size_t len)
{
    size_t pos = 0;
    // ...
    return (int)pos;  // Truncates if pos > INT_MAX
}
```

The comment at line 1543-1545 acknowledges this:
```c
/* ponytail: Return type is int, limiting buffer size to INT_MAX bytes (~2GB).
 * OSCORE payloads on constrained devices won't approach this limit. */
```

While the comment justifies the decision (OSCORE on constrained devices won't have 2GB payloads), the code should still protect against overflow:

```c
if (pos > (size_t)INT_MAX) {
    return -1;  // Treat as malformed
}
return (int)pos;
```

This is similar to the guards added elsewhere (lines 284-287 and 432-435).

Severity: Low - practically unreachable on constrained devices, but inconsistent with other guards in the same file.
